The game often doesn't save. When you stop and go back to it you find that you have yo do lrge sections again. At the end of a section it often crashes without saving. All progress is lost. It looks very nice, but I have to press a control in exactly the right place or it doesn't work. Controls are very frustrating. Some conversations go on far too long. The problems are very easy. You do what is obvious and move one. 3 or 4 times because it only saves 1 out of 4 times. Disappointing.

I enjoyed the story (and in particular, the various Easter eggs, especially for Twin Peaks), but the controls leave a lot to be desired and without using a walkthrough guide, there's not a logical enough connection between a lot of the steps to figure it out on your own without a LOT of trial and error.

I absolutely loved this game! It kept me interested and on my toes. Make sure you keep up with the story because there is a lot of necessary information in the dialogue with the people that you need to complete tasks. It does have some problems with the controls, you have to hit the keys multiple times to get the action to go through. It can get a bit difficult but if you just keep searching you'll eventually find the answers needed to finish each task.

Truthfully I was unhappy when I finished it. I liked that little town. Sure the voice acting wasn't the greatest, but it didn't have to be. One of my favorite point and click adventure games in the past 10 years.

I enjoyed it! It's engaging and I appreciate the multi-discipline study that went into it. There's a lot of quirky nerd-humor built in but you need a dry sense of humor to catch it all. Hit a glitch in Ch 4.2, my avatar suddenly vanished & needed to reboot but no other snags. The size of the picture is not optimal for phones but finished on my Samsung Note20 Ultra. The speed was frustratingly slow at times but give it a whirl!

I've cleaned my screen, removed my case, restarted the game, cleared my cache, and nothing seems to help. The intro (gas station) worked perfectly. But now, I'm unable to interact with anything. I'll keep the app until the next update in case it's a bug.
Probably not worth the time or effort, but some glimpses of brilliance.

Download it! I really enjoy this game, played through in one day. The setting is just gorgeous! I loved the humor in it, it was a teeny bit kitschy at times but that made it charming to me. There's a kind of in-game hint system and I could always go back to revisit something if I missed a detail which wasn't necessary but made the game stress-free. I really hope there will be a sequel!

I enjoyed this game. It reminded me a little of The Infamous Machine but with less clues for the gameplay and not as funny. The only issues I had with the game was the loading and some lengthy dialogue. But it wasn't a game changer for me and I think the graphics were worth it. For those of you who were complaining about the slow walking, you can double tap where you want the character to go and he walks faster.
